<keyLead id="30C095C44103FF85FF265417FA573A93" box="[151,1436,1145,1167]" pageId="13" pageNumber="57">
2 Median fins with orange-brown in proximal and median parts in males...................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C314D724103FF85FB115417FA573A93" box="[1184,1436,1145,1167]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Lacustricola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="margaritatus">
<emphasis id="B945EAE34103FF85FB115417FA573A93" box="[1184,1436,1145,1167]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="57">Lacustricola margaritatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
